HEADWORD: Patriotism
<hw>Pa"tri*ot*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>patriotisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>Love of country; devotion to the
welfare of one's country; the virtues and actions of a patriot; the
passion which inspires one to serve one's country.</def>
<rj><au>Berkley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

